step 1 : open terminal
step 2 : install python version
	code : sudo apt install python3.12-venv
step 3 : create virtual environment 
	 code : python3 -m venv [virtual_environment_name]
step 4 : active the virtual environment
	 code : source [virtual_environment_name]/bin/activate
step 5 : install python libraries
	 code : pip install [library_names]
	 -show all libraries : pip list
step 5 : switching environment
	code : deactivate
		then activate other virtual environment using step 3 code
